Krzywy Róg  is a settlement in the administrative district of Gmina Piecki, within Mrągowo County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-west of Piecki,  south of Mrągowo, and  east of the regional capital Olsztyn. It is located in Masuria.
The village was historically inhabited by Polish people since its foundation. The Polish noble families of Uklański and Wytyński lived in the village.
